description: Young RAY TORRES has finally made it to the safety of Sanctuary. Now begins a supposedly better life; which includes making new friends, adjusting to a strange environment and trying to figure how to get out of this whole Protege business. But, of course it's not going to be that easy. The Dark Paladin has a test Ray must survive and the Genociders' Z-10 Kilbot is still hunting him. What to do about that bothersome Mechanical Assassin? Find out how Ray resolves these problems in Sanctuary.

Young Ray Torres decides it's time to really test out his new powers and himself. The Genociders' Z-10 Kilbot has to be dealt with. It's a duel to the death. How can Ray foul this up? Plus Ray learns he's not stuck with the title: THE PROTÉGÉ. What name will he chose for himself? What other trouble can he get into? These and other questions will be answered in the SHOWDOWN!

Welcome to the BIG WEIRD – a network of pornocracies where GYNOIDS promise to fulfil the most baroque desires! Nana Plaza is Madame Kito's stake in The Big Weird …

… and Kito – mamasan, crime boss, and lady of dark influence with three generals and a cabinet minister in her bed – is ensconced in her penthouse atop the New Grace Hotel, brooding upon sex, death, and money …

… little suspecting that Ignatz Zwakh and Primavera Bobinski are soon to call upon her and demand reparation on behalf of the world of the de luxe that is also the world of DEAD GIRLS.
name: Going To A Go-Go

description:
Q: What’s eight-feet tall, has an exoskeleton made of chitin polymer and laser-proof spider silk, and a cybertronic brain that, if possessing the IQ of a retarded oyster, nevertheless has sufficient teraflops to implement the prime directive DESTROY ANYONE, AND ANYTHING, THAT HAS THE TEMERITY TO INTRUDE INTO MADAME KITO’S LAIR?

A: One of Madame Kito’s antiquated, but highly effective, Russian-built, hunter-killer sentinels.

Q: What’s five-feet-four-inches tall, has a bottle-blonde mane, luminous green eyes, and a body that – if superficially that of a human girl’s – has been infected, and robotically enhanced, by a nano-tech virus, so that its humanity is compromised by the superhuman?

A: A mutant, cyborg, or – to cite the demotic nomenclature – a doll, such as our anti-heroine, Primavera Bobinski.

Q: And what battle royale may ensue when creatures such as these – as disparate as they are alike – go toe-to-toe and clash high above the information-thick stew of Bangkok’s teeming streets?

A: To this, and much, much more, read …

… DEAD GIRLS!
name: Like A Bad Girl Should

description:
Inside the belly of the Doll!

For Ignatz Zwakh and his transgressive, teenage, techno-organic fix – the doll and all-round killing machine Primavera Bobinski – The Big Weird has suddenly got bigger, weirder.

Sucked into, trapped, and lost inside Primavera's quantum matrix, Bangkok has become a carnival, freakshow, and psychotronic theme park that threatens to imprison time, space, dolls and doll-junkies in a hall of mirrors filled with DEAD GIRLS!
name: In Dreams

description:
Let us travel, then, deeper into the city of the night, the dream city, the city of the dolls …

… and deeper still if Iggy and Primavera – our pair of star-crossed, sleepwalking, sixteen-year-old strays – are to escape a nanobot army manifest as a million Jack the Rippers, wake up, and return to something passing for home.

Yes, let us travel deeper, deeper, into the belly of the doll, to a sepulchral crossroads, its sexton and a magic toyshop filled with pretty, morbid toys …

… where a doll and a doll-dependent boy will learn of conspiracies, and of the past, present, and future of … Dead Girls!
name: Journey to the Centre of a Girl

description:
For Alice Liddell, Gilberte Swann, Kara Zor-El, Dolores Haze, and Wednesday Addams …

… for all girls, lost, heartbroken, and dangerous to know …

… but especially for Schrödinger’s girl aka Primavera Bobinski – a girl both alive and dead – whose cold, vital hand fervently clasps Iggy Zwakh’s own, now, as then, on the long, dark highway to Forever: a terminus befitting a girl lately risen from the dead, and her sidekick, a boy enraptured with …

… Dead Girls!
name: Just Like HEaven

description: A gothic tale based loosely on a play by August Strindberg, this is a surrealistic saga of a man who flashes back to the "defining moment" in his life where he found love, a future, terror and despair. A young man finds himself on destiny's door as he is pulled into an ancient family feud and is surprised to find out that somehow he is involved. Knowing that he has a special ability to sense things in others, young Isaac feels he is prepared for anything...and of course, he thought wrong. This is a supernatural drama of a man who reflects on the moment where his life was defined. Blessed (or cursed, depending on your view) with a special precognitive ability of sensing others emotions, he is pulled into a mysterious house and family that has led lives of treachery and deceit. He falls in love with the young woman of the house but can he save her against the overwhelming despair that infiltrates all those in the house? A lifetime of decisions controlled by a single moment. It is a life of pain and lost opportunities.
name: Part I

description: In this second issue of Ghost Sonata, we are taken back to the period when Isaac begins his exploration on his "defining moment" in life. Who is the mysterious man that offers to be his benefactor and how did he contribute to the death of Isaac's father? How is it that only Isaac can see the little flower girl? And unknown to Isaac, the beautiful house which he adores, holds dark secrets that will tear out his very soul.
name: Part II

description: The captivating tale of Ghost Sonata continues as Isaac finally gets to meet Adele and her family. But Hummell exposes bitterly held secrets that bind the household into a relationship of deceit. Layers of falsehood are shed away in a painful unveiling of truth, but can the truth be too high a price to pay?
name: Part III

description: The ramifications of a man's indecisiveness play out for the rest of his life as Isaac must deal with love lost forever. All the secrets are revealed but for some, they are too much too bear and life proves too painful to continue. For others, life ends up being an unfulfilled promise.
name: Part IV

description: Batman's loyal butler, Alfred, makes the ultimate sacrifice to save the Dynamic Duo. But can a strange scientist bring him back to life?
name: Mystery of the Outsider Part 1 of 4
